  "description": "A working procedure for locating the temporal middle in a specific case where it is being eliminated: identify the binary the structure offers, map the temporal middle the binary forecloses, trace how the structure handles temporal-middle subjects (invisibility, reframing, recoding), and note what the elimination accomplishes.",
  "name": "How to Locate the Temporal Middle Being Eliminated",
